E51.title: History of Dakota Supreme
E51.description: Dakota Supreme is one of if not the most powerful nations in the post war world. Originally it started as the Dakotan Principality of Bismarck which had recently formed as a Principality after the ND state government disbanded. The simple city state grew a monopoly on horses and used them to conquer surrounding territories, they did this with inspiration from and the tactics of the Great Khan such as their iconic tactic of demanding enemies submit or be completely destroyed. Once they conquered the territory known as North and South Dakota they declared themselves "The Supreme Khanate of Dakota" which is commonly referred to as "Dakota Supreme". They quickly used their tactics to take almost the entirety of the Great Plains...

E52.title: History of California
E52.description: California was the subject of a full scale Soviet Invasion during WW3, the government of California was disbanded and replaced with a Soviet occupational authority. However once nukes started going off the invasion forces quickly fell apart, different Russian and American military leaders broke off into factions forming small warlord states. Today these warlords successors still loot and raid across the region, some of them have crowned themselves, and some of them have been overthrown by Republicans. The only strong unified force in the region is the Reno Horde.

E53.title: History of Cascadia
E53.description: Cascadia is an area that has enjoyed relative stability after the war, while there was an attempted Soviet invasion during the war it happened near the end of it and thus wasnt able to gain much ground before loosing all command and dispersing. While there were temporarily warlords near the invasion grounds the state Governments of Washington and Oregon were able to retain control of their core lands and partner to destroy the warlords. Now they stand as beacons of democracy and the shattered American dream in this post nuclear war world...

E54.title: History of Idaho
E54.description: The Idahoan government went defunct almost immediately after the war leading to several states emerging. The mountainous areas of the Boise forest organized into a loose collection of people who paid tribute to a monarch, the king soon expanded out to other nearby mountains. In the main area of Idaho, the Treasure Valley a new Idahoan government was formed, it gained control over most of Snake river and began trading openly with all. Merchants refer to it as "Snake" due to the river it is centered around. The original Idahoan state government fled as Snake gained control, it quickly became extremely aggravated and fled to Eastern Oregon and declared itself the rightful and true Idahoan government. In the north the two main Indian tribes regained control of their lands.
